<p>Most businesses write a press release, submit it to one wire service, and call it done. That single submission reaches a fraction of the audience it could.</p>
<p>Press release submission sites, classified ad platforms, and digital PR services each serve a different purpose. Wire services reach journalists. Classified sites build backlinks. Digital PR platforms connect you directly with reporters looking for sources. Using all three creates a distribution system that compounds over time.</p>
<p>We compiled 173 submission sites across 8 categories. Every site on this list is active and accepting submissions as of April 2026. We included domain authority scores where available so you can prioritize high-value placements.</p>
