<h2>Free Press Release Submission Sites</h2>
<p>Free press release sites host your content and index it in search engines. They work like directories rather than active media pitching services. The backlink value and search visibility make them worth the effort.</p>
<p><strong>1. <a href="https://www.prlog.org/">PRLog</a></strong>. One of the most reliable free press release platforms. Strong domain authority (DA 84). Allows links, tagging, and branding at no cost. Press releases get indexed by Google quickly.</p>
<p><strong>2. <a href="https://www.openpr.com/">OpenPR</a></strong>. Europe-based platform serving a global audience. One free release every 30 days. Strong for SEO-oriented distribution through search engines and RSS feeds.</p>
<p><strong>3. <a href="https://pr.com/">PR.com</a></strong>. Free press release posting with business directory and job listing features. Releases are categorized by industry and distributed through the website and RSS feeds.</p>
<p><strong>4. <a href="https://www.prfree.org/">PRFree</a></strong>. Free press release submission with instant publishing. Supports live links for <a href="/blog/build-backlinks-for-blog/">backlink building</a>. Indexed by major search engines.</p>
<p><strong>5. <a href="https://www.free-press-release.com/">Free Press Release</a></strong>. Straightforward free submission. No account required for basic releases. DA 63 with consistent indexing.</p>
<p><strong>6. <a href="https://www.1888pressrelease.com/">1888PressRelease</a></strong>. Limited free tier with paid upgrades from $15. Free submissions get basic distribution and search engine indexing.</p>
<p><strong>7. <a href="https://www.prsync.com/">PRSync</a></strong>. Unlimited free submissions with no paid tier. Simple submission form. Good for consistent distribution without cost.</p>
<p><strong>8. <a href="https://www.pressreleasepoint.com/">PressReleasePoint</a></strong>. One free release every 3 months. Seven paid options for higher frequency. Good domain authority.</p>
<p><strong>9. <a href="https://www.express-press-release.net/">Express Press Release</a></strong>. Limited free tier with paid upgrades from $29. Free submissions include basic indexing and RSS distribution.</p>
<p><strong>10. <a href="https://www.przoom.com/">PRZoom</a></strong>. Free queue-based submissions. Paid options from $199 for faster processing and wider distribution.</p>
<p><strong>11. <a href="https://www.marketpressrelease.com/">MarketPressRelease</a></strong>. One free release per day. Additional releases cost $19 each. Good for regular product updates.</p>
<p><strong>12. <a href="https://www.forpressrelease.com/">ForPressRelease</a></strong>. Free submission with basic distribution. Categorized by industry for targeted visibility.</p>
<p><strong>13. <a href="https://www.pr-inside.com/">PR-Inside</a></strong>. Free for registered users. Multi-language support makes it useful for international distribution.</p>
